Class ImageProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • src.ImageProcessor

  • public class ImageProcessor
extends java.lang.Object
    Class that manages all image processing and comparison. Handles access and manipulation of frames for comparison.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Austin Musser, Kyle Cochran, Matthew Caixeiro

      • returnCurrentSpots

        public int[] returnCurrentSpots()
        A method to unify the processing methods of this class.
        Returns:

      • diffAsBinArray

        public int[][] diffAsBinArray()
        Takes in the current lot frame as an image and compares it to the lot reference image. Converts difference to a binary array that shows which pixels match.
        Returns:
        an array of integers that represent the state of each pixel (black/white) of the lot image difference with the reference image.

      • generateIsEmptyMatrix

        public int[] generateIsEmptyMatrix(int[][] binaryArray,
                                   int[][] lines)
        Cycles through binary array picture and looks for objects present in expected lot positions. If objects are present in a certain threshold percentage of the lot, the spot is marked full. This state is saved in an ordered array of spot states in the lot.
        Parameters:
        binaryArray - an array of integers that represents the two-tone lot difference image
        lines - an array of ordered coordinate pairs that represent the parking spot divisor lines
        Returns:
        an array that represents the state of each parking spot in a given lot

      • generateSpotMatrix

        private void generateSpotMatrix()
        Wrapper method to define the lines variable to our specific case

      • getSpotMatrix

        public int[][] getSpotMatrix()
        Identify where divisor lines are in current lot view.
        Returns:
        an array of coordinate pairs that represents the pixel location of parking spots divisor lines

      • IplImageToWritableImage

        public javafx.scene.image.WritableImage IplImageToWritableImage(org.bytedeco.javacv.Frame framesrc)
        Converts a JavaCV IPLImage object to a JavaFX WritableImage object to allow compatibility with JavaFX graphics. Code is a hybrid from the following sources: https://blog.idrsolutions.com/2012/11/convert-bufferedimage-to-javafx- image/ http://stackoverflow.com/questions/31873704/javacv-how-to-convert- iplimage-tobufferedimage
        Parameters:
        src - an IPLImage from the OpenCV/JavaCV library
        Returns:
        a WritableImage object (child of Java Image object) from the JavaFX library
